      "body" : "Well, bitcoind is the reference Bitcoin client, and a JSON-RPC server. Nothing to be changed about that.\r\n\r\nRegarding JSON-RPC clients: Bitcoin-Qt has an RPC console which can do everything bitcoind's RPC server can. But if you're just talking about CLI RPC clients, bitcoind is probably the most complete one, right now, unfortunately. I'm saying that earlier discussions about adding functionality to bitcoind-the-RPC-client resulted in suggestions to write a more featureful python RPC client instead.",
